Pennsylvania's sales tax is 6%, however I noticed on this order (that I wanted to submit before losing February rewards) I was charged more than that - 15%. (Thinking back to my order last month, I believe the tax seemed off to me then as well.) Tonight, when I used my "$10 to spend now" reward, I spent $11, so I was charged $1. With PA's sales tax it totaled $1.06, which was correct. Then, when I used my "$10 to spend in February" reward I received from last month's order, the total was also $11, so I was charged an additional dollar, making my teacher total $2.00. With PA sales tax $2x.06$0.12 which would be a total of $2.12, not the $2.30 I was charged. Now I understand it's only a few cents this time, but if it continues to happen and has happened to possibly hundreds of teachers, that money adds up. There may be a tax explanation that can be shared with me, or perhaps an algorithm is wrong and needs fixed. Thank you for your time.
